# ChurchLedger Design System

## Layout
- 12-column grid, max-w-7xl, px-6 py-6. gap-6 between sections.
- Tablet: 8 columns. Mobile: single-column stack.
- Every page: header (title + subtitle) → cards → actions top-right.

## Cards
- `rounded-2xl shadow-sm border p-6`. Group related content only.
- Header: title left, optional action right.

## Typography
- Page title: `text-2xl font-bold`. Subtitle: `text-sm text-muted-foreground`.
- KPI numbers: `text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight`. Labels: muted opacity.

## KPI Cards
- Use `StatCard` from `@/components/stat-card` with gradient + icon.
- Metric large, subtitle below, scannable at a glance.

## Tables
- shadcn `Table` with `rounded-md border overflow-x-auto` wrapper.
- Light row dividers, subtle hover. Actions right-aligned. Status as `Badge`.

## Charts
- Title + micro-summary subtitle ("£X of £Y budget used (Z%)").
- Empty state: icon + guidance text + CTA button. No heavy gridlines.

## Buttons
- Primary: visually prominent. Secondary: `variant="outline"`.
- Key actions: icon + text (e.g. `<FileText size={14} className="mr-1" />`).

## Empty States
- Never leave blank space unexplained.
- Show: reason why empty → suggested next action → CTA button.
- Tone: calm, encouraging, non-alarming.

## Status Badges
- Soft-colour `Badge`: Draft (outline), Approved (secondary), Posted/Submitted (default), Paid (default).

## Visual Tone
- Calm, professional, premium. Soft shadows, subtle borders, generous spacing.
- Avoid loud colours except KPI gradients and alerts.

## Accessibility
- Icons: `aria-hidden="true"` when decorative, `aria-label` when actionable.
- Buttons: visible hover/focus states. Colour contrast must meet WCAG AA.
- Forms: labels, helper text, clear validation feedback.

## Engineering
- Do not change existing data logic unless explicitly instructed.
- Reuse existing components. Keep components small and composable.
